div.p:
Demetrius of Byzantium relates that Crito removed
him from his workshop and educated him, being
struck by his beauty of soul;

Moreover, AnaxandridesComic poet;
ib. iii. 170. in his
Theseus says:

There are five kinds of speech, of which one is
that which politicians employ in the assemblies;
this is called political speech.

